quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  64,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth ňĻconstantlyňļ glorifies God. The kingdom is His, and all praise is for Him. For He is Most Capable of everything"
  64,2,"He is the One Who created you, yet some of you are disbelievers while some are believers. And God is All-Seeing of what you do"
  64,3,"He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. He shaped you ňĻin the wombňļ, perfecting your form. And to Him is the final return"
  64,4,He knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And He knows whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal. For God knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart
  64,5,"Have the stories of those who disbelieved before not reached you ňĻpagansňļ? They tasted the evil consequences of their doings, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  64,6,"That was because their messengers used to come to them with clear proofs, but they said ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúHow can humans be our guides?‚ÄĚ So they persisted in disbelief and turned away. And God was not in need ňĻof their faithňļ. For God is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  64,7,"The disbelievers claim they will not be resurrected. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYes, by my Lord, you will surely be resurrected, then you will certainly be informed of what you have done. And that is easy for God.‚ÄĚ"
  64,8,So believe in God and His Messenger and in the Light¬†We have revealed. And God is All-Aware of what you do
  64,9,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day He will gather you ňĻallňļ for the Day of Gathering‚ÄĒthat will be the Day of mutual loss and gain. So whoever believes in God and does good, He will absolve them of their sins and admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. That is the ultimate triumph"
  64,10,"As for those who disbelieve and reject Our revelations, they will be the residents of the Fire, staying there forever. What an evil destination"
  64,11,"No calamity befalls ňĻanyoneňļ except by God‚Äôs Will. And whoever has faith in God, He will ňĻrightlyňļ guide their hearts ňĻthrough adversityňļ. And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  64,12,"Obey God and obey the Messenger! But if you turn away, then Our Messenger‚Äôs duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ clearly"
  64,13,God‚ÄĒthere is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. So in God let the believers put their trust
  64,14,"O believers! Indeed, some of your spouses and children are enemies to you,¬†so beware of them. But if you pardon, overlook, and forgive ňĻtheir faultsňļ, then God is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  64,15,"Your wealth and children are only a test, but God ňĻaloneňļ has a great reward"
  64,16,"So be mindful of God to the best of your ability, hear and obey, and spend in charity‚ÄĒthat will be best for you. And whoever is saved from the selfishness of their own souls, it is they who are ňĻtrulyňļ successful"
  64,17,"If you lend to God a good loan, He will multiply it for you and forgive you. For God is Most Appreciative, Most Forbearing"
  64,18,"ňĻHe is theňļ Knower of the seen and unseen‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"